Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees or #grill{} to high. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Quarter the @heirloom grape tomatoes{8%ounce}. Roughly chop the @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves. Cut the @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Mince the @garlic{4%cloves}.

Boil the orzo: Add the @orzo pasta{12%ounce} to the boiling water. Cook ~{9-11%minutes}, until al dente. Drain.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Season the @sirloin steak{24%ounce} on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{} before adding it to the #pan{}. Cook ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until browned. Transfer steak to a #baking sheet{}, then place in the oven to finish cooking to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes}.

> TIP: You can also cook the steak on the grill if you have one!

Heat another large drizzle of olive oil in the same pan over medium heat. Add the garlic. Cook ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Add the tomatoes. Cook ~{1-2%minutes}, until slightly softened. Toss in the drained orzo, mozzarella, a large drizzle of olive oil, the @balsamic vinegar{4%tablespoon}, and ¾ of the parsley. Season with salt and pepper. Taste and adjust with more olive oil or balsamic vinegar, as needed.

Once the mozzarella has melted slightly, divide the caprese orzo salad between #plates{}. Thinly slice the seared steak, serve over the salad, and garnish with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!